00:25:13.480 --> 00:25:15.040 align:middle line:90%
They replicated the results.

00:25:15.040 --> 00:25:20.810 align:middle line:84%
There is some small
element beyond chance.

00:25:20.810 --> 00:25:23.120 align:middle line:90%
So they don't do that anymore.

00:25:23.120 --> 00:25:28.420 align:middle line:84%
But it's as if none of this
ever happened and the idea is,

00:25:28.420 --> 00:25:32.650 align:middle line:84%
like, well, you know, the
scientistic materialists--

00:25:32.650 --> 00:25:34.990 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not including
you among them,

00:25:34.990 --> 00:25:36.490 align:middle line:84%
at least for this
purpose, you know.

00:25:36.490 --> 00:25:40.850 align:middle line:84%
We're just-- ah, the--
the studies are flaws.

00:25:40.850 --> 00:25:42.050 align:middle line:90%
Ah, somehow, they're flawed.

00:25:42.050 --> 00:25:44.060 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, we're up against
a problem in science.

00:25:44.060 --> 00:25:45.160 align:middle line:90%
Science as a community.

00:25:45.160 --> 00:25:45.940 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:25:45.940 --> 00:25:48.810 align:middle line:84%
And communities do a lot
of conformity enforcing,

00:25:48.810 --> 00:25:51.420 align:middle line:84%
even though it is
antithetical to science,

00:25:51.420 --> 00:25:54.820 align:middle line:84%
absolutely against science,
to do conformity enforcing.

00:25:54.820 --> 00:25:57.510 align:middle line:84%
And I know-- you know, I'm
an outsider in this community

00:25:57.510 --> 00:26:00.140 align:middle line:84%
because I'm continually trying
to raise questions that it's

00:26:00.140 --> 00:26:02.320 align:middle line:90%
not considered polite to raise.

00:26:02.320 --> 00:26:07.340 align:middle line:84%
Nonetheless, I know that if I
went far enough out into space

00:26:07.340 --> 00:26:10.320 align:middle line:84%
to start bringing up the
JB Rhine stuff of my youth,

00:26:10.320 --> 00:26:12.970 align:middle line:84%
all the psychological studies
of my youth, the stuff

00:26:12.970 --> 00:26:16.270 align:middle line:84%
at Princeton University that
indicated that you actually

00:26:16.270 --> 00:26:18.830 align:middle line:84%
could have an influence
on physical objects--

00:26:18.830 --> 00:26:21.250 align:middle line:84%
a small, statistically
measurable influence

00:26:21.250 --> 00:26:24.930 align:middle line:84%
on physical objects-- if I
were to bring that stuff up,

00:26:24.930 --> 00:26:28.660 align:middle line:84%
that small amount of credibility
I need in order to raise

00:26:28.660 --> 00:26:30.430 align:middle line:84%
questions in the
scientific community

00:26:30.430 --> 00:26:31.820 align:middle line:90%
would disappear immediately.

00:26:31.820 --> 00:26:33.430 align:middle line:84%
And as a consequence,
these are things

00:26:33.430 --> 00:26:35.360 align:middle line:90%
I just have to stay away from.

00:26:35.360 --> 00:26:38.150 align:middle line:84%
Even I who try to do
everything in my power

00:26:38.150 --> 00:26:41.060 align:middle line:84%
to be courageous
and take chances

00:26:41.060 --> 00:26:44.130 align:middle line:84%
know that there's
only so far I can go.

00:26:44.130 --> 00:26:48.230 align:middle line:84%
But I would go there if I felt
it was going to be productive.

00:26:48.230 --> 00:26:50.900 align:middle line:84%
Instead, I'd rather go where
you go, with [INAUDIBLE]

00:26:50.900 --> 00:26:54.590 align:middle line:84%
and with my own experiences
with peyote and LSD,

00:26:54.590 --> 00:26:57.430 align:middle line:84%
which admittedly I only
